#Text=Te Anau
#Text=Te Anau is a small town on the shore of Lake Te Anau , in the Southland region of the South Island of New Zealand .
#Text=It is the gateway to Fiordland and Fiordland National Park .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Turn off the Queenstown - Invercargill highway just north of Lumsden onto SH94 .
#Text=Te Anau also has an airstrip for light sightseeing aircraft .
#Text=Most travellers use Te Anau as a jumping-off point to Milford Sound and Doubtful Sound .
#Text=Allow 2 hours to reach Milford Sound from Te Anau .

#Text=There are lots of scenic stops along the way , but not much else , so stop at Fresh Choice for snacks and be sure to fill up your gas tank , as there is limited petrol available in Milford Sound .
#Text=By bus
#Text=InterCity Coachlines run buses to Te Anau from Christchurch via Dunedin , Queenstown and Milford Sound .
#Text=From Invercargill
#Text=a change at Gore is required .
#Text=Tracknet run buses from Queenstown and Invercargill .
#Text=This is also available as a combined ferry and bus ticket from Stewart Island by Stewart Island Experience .
#Text=Tracknet have services to and from some walking routes .
#Text=See
#Text=Te Anau-Au Caves .
#Text=Approximately 2.3 hr total .
#Text=A boat trip and guided tour into the Aurora Caves system by walking path and small boats within the cave itself where you will see thousands of glow worms .
#Text=The caves are only accessible by boat , and Real Journeys operates a quality catamaran for a 30-minute cruise each way .
#Text=You 'll spend approximately 35 min underground , where you will see some spectacular underground waterfalls , some high ceilings , and many other interesting things with a professional guide .
#Text=It is not suitable for everyone .
#Text=You will have to bend over considerably at the entrance , which is only 1 m high for 3-4 m. Promotions often apply .
#Text=$63/adult , $20/child .
#Text=Lake Te Anau ( Te Ana-au ) .
#Text=" The cave of swirling water " , it is the second-largest lake by surface area in New Zealand ( after Lake Taupo ) and the largest in the South Island .
#Text=North Fiord , Middle Fiord and South Fiord are the only inland NZ fiords .
#Text=Lake Marian .
#Text=Off Hollyford Road on the way to Milford lies one of the most beautiful places on earth .
#Text=Te Anau Wildlife Centre ( 1 km ( c. 10-min walk ) from the Fiordland National Park Visitor Centre towards Manapouri ) .
#Text=Dawn to dusk .
#Text=A short walk from downtown , the Te Anau Wildlife Centre provides the unique opportunity to view some of New Zealand 's rarest endangered birds .
#Text=Be sure to see the takahe , a large flightless bird with beautiful blue plumage and an enormous red beak .
#Text=With only 225 takahe left in New Zealand , this is perhaps your only opportunity to see this majestic bird .
#Text=Free , but donations are appreciated .
#Text=Do
#Text=Tramp any of the many tracks located in the area .
#Text=Te Anau is n't called the walking capital of the world for no reason !
#Text=The major tracks that can be started from the surrounding area include the following " Great Walks " :
#Text=Kepler Track .
#Text=This track starts from near Te Anau , and the section around the lake to Brod Bay and back makes a pleasant gentle day walk .
#Text=The complete track ( a circular route ) usually takes 3 or 4 days and climbs to 1470 m.
#Text=Routeburn Track .
#Text=Milford Track .
#Text=This has been described as the greatest walk in the world .
#Text=It is very popular and the many dates are fully booked within hours of booking opening in June for the following summer .
#Text=The track starts with a ferry ride from Te Anau Downs , and there are connecting shuttle buses available .
#Text=The track takes 4 days if you are walking independently .
#Text=Do n't miss out on going to Milford Sound , taking a cruise , and enjoying the scenic wonderland .
#Text=For once it 's probably better to take a bus , they do n't rush it and you get good quality commentary .
#Text=Take a day walk somewhere - Lake Marian for example .
#Text=If you do n't have gear , you can hire it from Bev 's Tramping Gear Hire .
#Text=Cruise Te Anau .
#Text=A boutique cruise to the South Fiord of Lake Te Anau and a gentle bush/nature walk to discover the Hidden Lakes .
#Text=Westray Horse Treks , 55 Ramparts Road , ☏ +643 249-9079 .
#Text=9AM , 1PM and 4:30PM .
#Text=$ 75 .
#Text=Buy
#Text=The Gateway .
#Text=Buy and rent DVDs , video games , and CDs , but a terrible selection of used books .
#Text=Friendly staff .
#Text=Outside Sports , 38-40 Milford Rd , ☏ +643 249-8195 .
#Text=Buy or hire most tramping gear you may need for one of the nearby tracks .
#Text=Eat
#Text=There are several decent places to eat , considering the size of Te Anau .
#Text=La Toscana .
#Text=For pizza , pasta and both Italian & NZ wines .
#Text=Miles Better Pies , 2 Milford Crescent , ☏ +6432499044 .
#Text=7AM-3PM .
#Text=Specialist pie shop that has a range of fresh pies , sandwiches , cake slices and other treats , and great coffee , all to take away .
#Text=The pies are packed with meat . <$ 10 .
#Text=Redcliff , 12 Mokonui St , ☏ +643 249-7431 .
#Text=Summer : restaurant 5PM-9:30PM , bar 3PM till late .
#Text=Serves food and drink .
#Text=Warm atmosphere , cozy pub-feel and the rustic small-town kindly atmosphere you would expect in NZ .
#Text=$ 30 .
#Text=Sandfly Cafe , 9 The Lane .
#Text=Country-style cafe open for breakfast and brunch .
#Text=The local supermarkets are a cheap alternative if you 're self-catering .
#Text=Fresh Choice , 5 Milford Crescent .
#Text=7AM-9PM .
#Text=Te Anau 's main supermarket , also the best place to buy beer and wine .
#Text=Four Square , 30 Town Centre .
#Text=M - F 7:30AM – 8PM , Sa 8AM – 8PM , Su 8AM – 7:30PM .
#Text=Smaller supermarket with groceries and some prepared meals .
#Text=Drink
#Text=The three main venues in Te Anau are The Ranch , The Moose and Redcliff , in order of the age groups most likely to be found at each location .
#Text=There is also a working men 's club for the older generations .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=During December and January , bookings are essential !
#Text=While bed and breakfasts , hotels , and backpackers abound in Te Anau , they will fill up and the nearest accommodation could be as far away as Gore .
